article.headline: Old Dominion 66, Toledo 35
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Abdi Lidonde and Brian Henderson each scored 11 points as Old Dominion beat Toledo 66-35 Friday night. Toledo (1-2) hit only 5 of 31 field goals, 16 percent, in the first half, and trailed 29-11 at the half. The Rockets finished with 21 percent shooting for the game, compared to better than 47 percent shooting for Old Dominion (2-0). Old Dominion dominated in the paint, 37-16, off the fast break, 21-2, and in points off turnovers, scoring 16-8 despite having two fewer turnovers than the Rockets. Gerald Lee added 10 points for Old Dominion. Brandon Johnson brought down 10 rebounds, and Sam Harris had nine. Jonathan Amos led Toledo with nine points. Jerrah Young added nine rebounds.
